FAIRY TALES DO COME TRUE...AND I WAS LUCKY ENOUGH TO WITNESS IT 6-29-2019

I’m not one usually to write novels on IG (mainly bc I’m a bad writer and was forced to be in ESL for most of middle school) but I will take this moment to acknowledge the incredible blessings I’ve been given in the last decade. What started out to be a farfetched dream, became a reality and I couldn’t have done it without all partnership and support from those who believed in me.

When I first started, all I wanted was to see ppl be able to wear the things I designed. A decade later, I have realized that my mission and passion is far beyond that. The opportunity to create meaningful work and show what an immigrant American story can look like in 2020 has been an absolute privilege.  Making beautiful things and helping ppl look and feel their best, is not only a dream come true, but being able to bring ppl together while doing so, has become the most rewarding aspect.

So I want to say thank you again, to all my fans/customers/colleagues/mentors/friends/family and even critics, for joining me on this journey and making me a braver, more daring individual to pursue my wildest dreams and share this story with all of you. 
PS. THIS collage took a lot of patience and WiFi to gather, so excuse the sloppy cropping, but I promise to get better ❤️
